LEGIONELLOSIS, HOTEL - SCANDINAVIA EX THAILAND (PHUKET):ALERT
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Thu, 11 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Helsingin Sanomat [edited]
<http://www.hs.fi/english/article/Nordic+tourists+acquire+Legionnaires+disease+in+Thailand/1135224234107>

The transfers of hundreds of Finnish tourists have begun from a hotel
in Phuket to other accommodation, following an outbreak of
Legionnaires' disease in the popular beach resort hotel.
Two Finns, a Norwegian, and 2 Swedish tourists have fallen ill with
pneumonia caused by _Legionella_ bacteria, after having stayed at the
Phuket Grand Tropicana Hotel in Patong Beach, Phuket. All had been at
the hotel in the period since 20 Nov 2006.
The National Public Health Institute has recommended the Finnish
travel operator Aurinkomatkat should transfer all its clients from
the hotel as soon as possible. The hotel must not be used until the
water and air-conditioning systems have been cleaned and appropriate
certifications on the completion of the measures have been received.
The National Public Health Institute is urging all persons who have
been resident in the hotel since 20 Nov 2006 and have fallen ill with
fever of more than 38 degrees C, either during the trip or within 14
days after leaving the hotel, to go to the doctor as soon as
possible. However, if the symptoms have already disappeared, there is
no need to seek medical care.
Pneumonia caused by the _Legionella_ bacterium can be fatal for the
elderly with heart and lung conditions, says epidemiologist Tran Minh
Nhu Nguyen from the National Public Health Institute.
The Grand Tropicana has a constant quota of 125 rooms for Finnish
travelers, and currently, more than 300 tourists are being
accommodated at the hotel, reports Tom Selanniemi of Aurinkomatkat.
Other accommodations have already been found for part of the guests,
even though it is not an easy task with the Chinese New Year being
celebrated soon.
--
